{"BR": {"BR_id": "186", "BR_author": "qubvel", "BRopenT": "2019-02-11T19:18:39Z", "BRcloseT": "2019-02-26T19:44:09Z", "BR_text": {"BRsummary": "RandomScale, ShiftScaleRotate strange \"scale\" aug behavior", "BRdescription": "\n <denchmark-h:h2>\ud83d\udc1b Bug</denchmark-h>\n \n \n \n RandomScale:\n -- docs: \"scale_limit ((float, float) or float): scaling factor range. If scale_limit is a single float value, the\n range will be (1 - scale_limit, 1 + scale_limit). Default: 0.1.\"\n -- params: {'scale': random.uniform(1 + self.scale_limit[0], 1 + self.scale_limit[1])}\n \n \n ShiftScaleRotate:\n -- docs: \"scale_limit ((float, float) or float): scaling factor range. If scale_limit is a single float value, the\n range will be (-scale_limit, scale_limit). Default: 0.1.\"\n -- params: {'scale': random.uniform(1 + self.scale_limit[0], 1 + self.scale_limit[1])}\n \n \n Docs are different but params are the same.\n Intuitively specifying scale_limit=(0.5, 2.0) I was expecting following sizes for the image with shape 224\u0445224:\n \n min 128x128\n max 448x448\n \n But I got:\n \n min: 336x336\n max: 672x672\n \n I understand it as range(1.5, 3)\n <denchmark-h:h2>Environment</denchmark-h>\n \n \n Albumentations version 0.1.12 (latest)\n \n \t"}, "comments": {}}, "commit": {"commit_id": "c62f37bb355f3386366c6859b904bfb36cd5de43", "commit_author": "BloodAxe", "commitT": "2019-02-26 21:43:00+02:00", "commit_complexity": {"commit_NLOC": "0.0", "commit_CCN": "0.0", "commit_Nprams": "0.0"}, "changed_files": {"file_0": {"file_change_type": "MODIFY", "file_Nmethod": 2, "file_old_name": "albumentations\\augmentations\\transforms.py", "file_new_name": "albumentations\\augmentations\\transforms.py", "file_complexity": {"file_NLOC": "1012", "file_CCN": "129", "file_NToken": "5874"}, "hunks": {"hunk_0": {"Ismethod": 1, "added_lines": "394", "deleted_lines": "394", "method_info": {"method_name": "get_params", "method_params": "self", "method_startline": "393", "method_endline": "394", "